text: I’m in Edmonton tonight to kick things off with our incredible team! We’ve done a lot together these past four years, but the truth is, we’re just getting started. Watch live: http://lpc.ca/app5 #ChooseForward

J’ai hâte de parler de mon plan pour aider les Canadiens à améliorer leur quotidien !pic.twitter.com/WQBjvJWEP6

Avoir un enfant est un moment marquant, mais entraîne des coûts. Les parents s’inquiètent pour l’avenir. Ils ont besoin d’aide et Trudeau montre qu’on ne peut pas lui faire confiance. Nous allons rendre les prestations de maternité libres d’impôt pour aider les parents.pic.twitter.com/L4eSJzq2u4

Having a child is an exciting milestone, but it comes with added costs. Parents are worried about the future. They are looking for help and Trudeau has proven he cannot be trusted to deliver it. We will make maternity benefits tax-free to help parents get ahead.pic.twitter.com/JqAH7UwgTV

1/ L’une des raisons de l’existence du @ppopulaireca est qu’il y a plus d’un an, j’ai dénoncé le culte de la diversité de Trudeau: la pratique visant à catégoriser chacun selon l’origine ethnique, couleur de peau, sexe, identité de genre, orientation sexuelle, religion, etc.

3/ All the other parties support the cult of diversity. The PPC is the only party with the courage to push back. The PPC is the only one defending the dignity or each individual and focusing on what unites us as Canadians. Join us if you agree!https://www.peoplespartyofcanada.ca

2/ This provoked hysterical reactions. But instead of agreeing with my conservative position and defending me, @AndrewScheer and several Conservative MPs disavowed me. They were afraid. That’s when I finally decided to leave this intellectually and morally corrupt party.

1/ One of the reasons the @peoplespca exists is that over a year ago, I denounced Trudeau’s cult of diversity: the divisive practice of categorizing everyone according to their ethnicity, skin colour, sex, gender identity, sexual orientation, religion, etc.
